    "body": "### Problem\n\nEntering Insert mode in prompt buffer acts like by `normal o` regardless of the way. \n\nOriginal problem: https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope.nvim/issues/3617\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nlocal function init()\n  local api = vim.api\n  local buf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n  api.nvim_open_win(buf, true, {height = 1, width = 40, relative = 'editor', col = 0, row = 0})\n\n  local prompt = '> '\n  vim.bo[buf].buftype = 'prompt'\n  vim.fn.prompt_setprompt(buf, prompt)\n  api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, false, {prompt .. 'query'})\n  vim.cmd.startinsert()\nend\n\n-- schedule because https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12295 is not considered a bug\nvim.schedule(init)\n```\n\nThis is not minimal, but shows confusing effect in one-line window containing prompt buffer. A possible minimal alternative is [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36194#issuecomment-3857961906) (@shadmansaleh):\n\n```lua\nlocal buf = 1\nlocal prompt = '> '\nvim.bo[buf].buftype = 'prompt'\nvim.fn.prompt_setprompt(buf, prompt)\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, false, {prompt .. 'query'})\nvim.api.nvim_feedkeys('A', 'n', false)\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe redundant new line is not added.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2209+gdb133879b2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nreom repo",
